From bf09f91b1df388dc679a896513649ad00bbdf987 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Philipp Stanner <phasta@kernel.org>
Date: Wed, 23 Apr 2025 09:53:27 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] ALSA: fm801: Use pure devres PCI
Git-commit: bf09f91b1df388dc679a896513649ad00bbdf987
Patch-mainline: v6.16-rc1
References: jsc#PED-14430 jsc#PED-14297 jsc#PED-14024

pci_request_regions() is a hybrid function which becomes managed if
pcim_enable_device() was called before. This hybrid nature is deprecated
and should not be used anymore.

Replace pci_request_regions() with the always-managed function
pcim_request_all_regions().

Signed-off-by: Philipp Stanner <phasta@kernel.org>
Reviewed-by: Andy Shevchenko <andriy.shevchenko@linux.intel.com>
Signed-off-by: Takashi Iwai <tiwai@suse.de>
Link: https://patch.msgid.link/20250423075346.45907-10-phasta@kernel.org

---
 sound/pci/fm801.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/sound/pci/fm801.c b/sound/pci/fm801.c
index 7f4834c2d5e6..f283256eda0d 100644
--- a/sound/pci/fm801.c
+++ b/sound/pci/fm801.c
@@ -1191,7 +1191,7 @@ static int snd_fm801_create(struct snd_card *card,
 	chip->dev = &pci->dev;
 	chip->irq = -1;
 	chip->tea575x_tuner = tea575x_tuner;
-	err = pci_request_regions(pci, "FM801");
+	err = pcim_request_all_regions(pci, "FM801");
 	if (err < 0)
 		return err;
 	chip->port = pci_resource_start(pci, 0);
